{"lemma":"أَشْأَم","slug":"أَشْأَم","root":"ش.#.م","root_slug":"ش-_-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-م","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21494","n21505"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%92%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%85"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of مشؤوم"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of مشؤوم:; more/most unfortunate, unlucky, unprosperous"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21494","headword_ar":"اشام","root":"$A^m","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He desired the left:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayomana","text_ar":"اَيْمَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ he desired the right. ” (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ymn","text_ar":"يمن"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aA^om","text_ar":"الشَّاْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Syria"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K, TA: [see also 3:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went thither:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayomana","text_ar":"اَيْمَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ he came to El-Yemen. ” (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^a$oA^amahu","text_ar":"مَا اَشْاَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How unlucky,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inauspicious, is he!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the vulgar say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayo$amahu","text_ar":"اَيْشَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n21505","headword_ar":"اَشْاَمُ","root":"$A^m","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, unlucky, inauspicious, unfortunate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unprosperous"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. The Arabs say,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1491},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oA^amu kul~i A@moriy^ K bayona laHoyayohi","text_ar":"اَشْاَمُ كُلِّ ا@مْرِي ٍ بَيْنَ لَحْيَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Meyd, TA,) as some relate it, or, as others relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fak~ayohi","text_ar":"فَكَّيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means the same, (Meyd,) [app. meaning accord. to the TA,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The most unlucky thing of every man is between his two jaws,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two lateral portions of his lower jaw;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oA^amu","text_ar":"اَشْاَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uw^omN","text_ar":"شُوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the unluckiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; and in a similar manner [the contr.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayomanu","text_ar":"اَيْمَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used [in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yumon","text_ar":"يُمْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so says AHeyth: (Meyd:) the prov. meaning the tongue. (AHeyth, TA.) The fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uw^omaY","text_ar":"شُوْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyadu","text_ar":"اليَدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~uw^omaY","text_ar":"الشُّوْمَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The left hand"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlyumonaY","text_ar":"اليُمْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~imaAlu","text_ar":"الشِّمَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is said in a trad., respecting camels,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yaA^otiY xayoruhaA A_il~aA mino","text_ar":"لَا يَاْتِى خَيْرُهَا اـِلَّا مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibihaA AlA^a$oA^ami","text_ar":"جَانِبِهَا الاَشْاَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their goodness comes not save from their left side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e. they are milked and mounted only from the left side. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$ow^uwmN","text_ar":"مَشْوُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b4-  Zuheyr, in the following saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fatunotajo lakumo gilomaAna A^a$oA^ama kul~uhumo\n                      \n                     \n                        kaA^aHomari EaAd K vum~a turoDiEo fatafoTimo"},{"kind":"text","text":"uses it in the sense of the inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uw^om","text_ar":"شُوْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gilomaAna $uw^omK","text_ar":"غِلْمَانَ شُوْمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, and EM p. 124:) he says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. war,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will bring forth for you boys of ill luck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil omen; all of them like Ahmar of' Ád: then it will suckle"},{"kind":"text","text":"these boys,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and wean"},{"kind":"text","text":"them: by Ahmar of ' Ád, he means Ahmar of Thamood, for Ahmar was the surname of him who hamstrung the she-camel of Sálih, and his name was Kudár: he says thus for the sake of the measure: or, as some say, Thamood were called 'Ád-el-Ákhireh. (EM.)"}],"source_refs":["Meyd","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}